<2ND_LINE>AM-Oscars-List, 3rd Ld - Writethru, a07767,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Partial List of 60th Academy Award Winners.</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with next three awards.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a partial list of Oscar winners at
Monday night's 60th annual Academy Awards ceremony.
   1. VISUAL EFFECTS: ``Innerspace,'' Dennis Muren, William George,
Harley Jessup and Kenneth Smith.
   2. SUPPORTING ACTRESS: Olympia Dukakis, ``Moonstruck.''
   3. ART DIRECTION: ``The Last Emperor,'' Ferdinando Scarfiotti;
Set Direction, Bruno Cesari.
   4. CINEMATOGRAPHY: ``The Last Emperor,'' Vittorio Storaro.
   5. ANIMATED SHORT FILM:``The Man Who Planted Trees,'' Frederic
Back.
   6. DOCUMENTARY SHORT SUBJECT: ``Young at Heart,'' Sue Marx and
Pamela Conn.
   7. DOCUMENTARY FEATURE: ``The Ten-Year Lunch: The Wit and Legend
of the Algonquin Round Table,'' Aviva Slesin.
   8. SOUND: ``The Last Emperor,'' Bill Rowe and Ivan Sharrock.
   9. SUPPORTING ACTOR: Sean Connery, ``The Untouchables.''
   10. FILM EDITING: ``The Last Emperor,'' Gabriella Cristiani.
   11. ORIGINAL SONG: ``(I've Had) The Time of My Life,'' ``Dirty
Dancing;'' music by Franke Previte, John DeNicola and Donald
Markowitz; lyric by Franke Previte.
   12. ORIGINAL SCORE: ``The Last Emperor,'' Ryuichi Sakamoto,
David Byrne and Cong Su.
   13. ACTOR: Michael Douglas, ``Wall Street.''
   Announced in advance:
   IRVING G. THALBERG: Director Billy Wilder.
   SPECIAL ACHIEVEMENT: Sound effects editing team on ``Robocop.''
   GORDON E. SAWYER: Movie sound specialist Fred Hynes.
</TEXT>
