<2ND_LINE>AM-Murder Arrest,0209</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Arrested in Brooklyn On Maryland Murder Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 28-year-old man wanted for five murders in
Maryland has been arrested after being spotted on a television show
on fugitives.
   Carl Dunstrum was arrested late Saturday using warrant murders
issued by Prince George's County in Maryland, said Sgt. Maurice
Howard, a department spokesman.
   In addition to the five killings for which he was sought in
Maryland, Dunstrum was being questioned by Brooklyn detectives in
connection with a sixth killing in that borough, a department
spokeswoman, Sgt. Diane Kubler, said Sunday.
   The Brooklyn victim was Patrick Ford, 17, who was found shot
once in the head on Nov. 26, Kubler said.
   About 30 police raided the basement apartment where Dunstrum was
staying Saturday evening.
   Dunstrum was recently featured on the Fox network television
show ``America's Most Wanted,'' and the show helped lead to his
arrest, Howard said.
   He was one of three New Yorkers wanted in the execution-style
slayings of of four men and a woman Jan. 22 at an apartment complex
in Landover, Md. Police at the time said the slayings appeared to
be drug related.
   One woman shot in the neck survived the attack.
</TEXT>
