<HEAD>Beijing To Hold First Beauty Contest `China Style'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Beijing plans to host its first beauty pageant
since the Communist takeover, the official China Daily said today.
   Long Xinmin, head of the Beijing Television Studio co-sponsoring
the event, said 10 Beijing ``girls of youth and elegance'' will be
selected through a television contest and awarded ``youth vitality
prizes,'' the report said.
   He said judges will put ``as much emphasis on the participants'
knowledge, performing technique, and moral character as on their
appearance and dress.'' The contest is open to women, married and
unmarried, who are residents of Beijing and between the ages of 17
and 27.
   The contest will end in June, and the finals will be televised.
   The first beauty contest in China since the takeover occurred in
Canton in 1985. The government was sensitive about it at the time
because the Communist Party says concern for physical appearance is
decadent and vain.
</TEXT>
