<HEAD>Nims Elected Chief Judge of Tax Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Arthur L. Nims III, who has served on the U.S.
Tax Court since 1979, has been elected chief judge for a two-year
term, the court announced today.
   Nims, 65, a native of Oklahoma City, will succeed Samuel B.
Sterrett, who is retiring next month.
   Nims, who practiced law briefly in Macon, Ga., and Newark, N.J.,
served four years with the Internal Revenue Service.
