<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Italy-Cuomo     04-11 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy-Cuomo,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Arrest Made In Killing Of Cousin Of New York Governor's Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MESSINA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities arrested a man Monday in the
killing of the cousin of the wife of New York Gov. Mario Cuomo,
police said.
   Francesco Gitto, 50, cousin of Matilda Cuomo, was shot to death
Dec. 14 in a sporting goods store. A store employee, Natale
Lavorini, 60, also was slain.
   Salvadore Imbesi, an escaped convict considered by police to be
the ``right hand'' of jailed Mafia boss Natale Chofalo, was
arrested at his sister's house in Giaveno, a small town on the
outskirts of Turin.
   Police spokesman Antolini Giovanni said Imbesi is accused of
complicity in four murders, extortion, associating with criminals
and escape.
   Imbesi was serving an eight-year sentence for robbery when he
was given permission in February 1987 to leave the prison in
Messina to visit his sick mother. He never returned.
   Police have said they don't know the motive for the Gitto
killing.
</TEXT>
