<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--NewAreaCode     04-11 0125</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--New Area Code,0126</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Florida's Burgeoning Growth Causes Area Code Split</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Telephone customers from Boca Raton
to Orlando will get a new area code, 407, Saturday night at
midnight.
   ``We're running out of telephone numbers,'' Southern Bell
spokesman Buck Passmore said.
   The new 407 area code will be assigned to about 2.1 million
telephone numbers, while almost 1.7 million in Broward, Dade and
Monroe counties will keep 305.
   Although the area code officially changes this weekend, people
will have a year to get used to it.
   For two months, callers may dial either area code. For 10 months
after that, if the wrong area code is dialed, the caller will hear
a recording that advises the correct area code.
</TEXT>
