<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Crops-Oranges     04-11 0144</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Crops-Oranges,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Orange Crop Ahead of Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's orange harvest for the 1987-88
crop season is estimated at 199.4 million boxes, fractionally less
than forecast in March but 9 percent more than last year, the
Agriculture Department said Monday.
   Florida production, based on April 1 indications, was estimated
at 140.6 million boxes, up slightly from March and 17 percent more
than last season's crop.
   The California harvest was estimated at 55 million boxes,
unchanged from the March forecast but 6 percent less than in
1986-87. The Arizona crop was indicated at 2.3 million boxes, down
25 percent from the January forecast, which had been carried
forward into February and March, and 27 percent below last season.
   Texas production, at 1.49 million boxes, was down 4 percent from
last month's forecast but was up 70 percent from 1986-87's harvest.

</TEXT>
