   A Manhattan lawyer charged Monday that he was
beaten without cause by a U.S. Secret Service agent traveling in a
motorcade with Democratic presidential candidate Sen. Albert Gore
Jr.
   An official of the service maintained that the agent appeared to
have acted properly after Christopher Gorayeb, 30, ``jumped in
front'' of a Secret Service car.
   But Gorayeb said he was crossing the street legally when he was
