<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--See-Through Arrest,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman in See-Through Clothes Arrested After Near-Wrecks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PEORIA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 21-year-old woman was arrested after her
see-through, fish-net attire was blamed for causing several
near-accidents as she walked down the street.
   Peoria police said Dolly May Jane McCloud of East Peoria was
arrested Saturday on charges of public indecency and disorderly
conduct, as well as obstructing police.
   According to police reports, an unidentified driver reported
several motorists nearly collided when they suddenly slowed to look
at Ms. McCloud.
   Sgt. Phillip Benne said Ms. McCloud was wearing a see-through,
fish-net body suit that exposed her chest. She was covered by other
clothes from the waist down, Benne said.
   Benne said he saw three motorists slam on their brakes, honk
their horns and wave at Ms. McCloud, who was taken to the Peoria
County Jail and released after posting $100 cash bond. She is
scheduled to appear in court on May 2.
