<HEAD>Emhart, Price Pfister Agree To Merge In $215 Million Deal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FARMINGTON, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Emhart Corp. has agreed to acquire
Price Pfister Inc. in a deal valued at about $215 million, it was
announced Monday.
   Under a definitive merger pact approved by the board of
directors of both companies, Emhart said it would purchase each of
Price Pfister's 11.4 million outstanding common shares for about
$18.50.
   The merger requires formal approval by a majority of Price
Pfister's stockholders.
   Based in Pacoima, Calif., Price Pfister manufactures
conventional and decorative faucets, valves, and fittings. It has
about 1,600 employees.
   Farmington-based Emhart is a diversified, multinational producer
of industrial and consumer products, and a provider of information
and electronic systems technology services for the government and
commercial markets.
 
